OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWorkers in Iraq given day  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Foff as heat hits 50C       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, State employees in many parts of Iraq  
OL,6, have been given a day off work as      
OL,7, temperatures rise to above 50C (122F)  
OL,8, in several areas, local media report.  
OL,10,FSeveral of the country's cities topped 
OL,11,Fthe list of the hottest places in the  
OL,12,Fworld on Thursday.                     
OL,14,FAs a result of the scorching heat, at  
OL,15,Fleast 10 provinces suspended work for  
OL,16,Fmost state employees, Kurdistan24 said.
OL,18,FA heatwave in the country has been     
OL,19,Fongoing since mid-July and is forecast 
OL,20,Fto continue.                           
